00:00:06:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:06:180000.Dialogue: It's from Game of Thrones. What do you think?

00:00:09:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:09:210000.Dialogue: I don't know. If we're going to start a fantasy sword collection-- and I've long thought we should--

00:00:17:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:17:130000.Dialogue: is this really the sword to start with?

00:00:19:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:19:180000.Dialogue: What did you have in mind?

00:00:21:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:21:110000.Dialogue: Well, off the top of my head, I'd have to go with Excalibur.

00:00:25:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:25:190000.Dialogue: It gives you the right to rule England.

00:00:28:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:28:140000.Dialogue: It would be a replica of a movie prop.

00:00:31:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:31:090000.Dialogue: Fair enough. It'd give you the right to rule a replica of England.

00:00:36:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:36:230000.Dialogue: Well, they don't have an Excalibur here, so what do you want to do?

00:00:40:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:40:230000.Dialogue: Mm. Tough decision. There's no weaponry from Lord of the Rings forged in a Chinese sweatshop?

00:00:49:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:49:180000.Dialogue: Just Bilbo Baggins' sword over there.

00:00:52:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:52:210000.Dialogue: Two grown men with a hobbit's dagger; wouldn't we look silly?

00:01:00:150000.Speaker: Stuart
00:01:00:150000.Dialogue: Oh, I see you guys have found my little treasure.

00:01:12:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:12:010000.Dialogue: What do you want for it?

00:01:13:150000.Speaker: Stuart
00:01:13:150000.Dialogue: Oh, it's hard to put a price on something that's a copy of something that was on pay cable.

00:01:19:120000.Speaker: Stuart
00:01:19:120000.Dialogue: But for my friends, let's say 250?

00:01:24:050000.Speaker: Stuart
00:01:24:050000.Dialogue: Well, it's a limited edition. They only made 8,000 of these bad boys.

00:01:28:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:28:120000.Dialogue: Only 8,000? We're wasting precious time. Buy it.

00:01:32:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:32:020000.Dialogue: Hang on. Can you do any better?

00:01:35:230000.Speaker: Stuart
00:01:35:230000.Dialogue: Are you kidding? I'm already giving you the friends and family discount.

00:01:39:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:39:010000.Dialogue: Oh, did you hear that? We're getting the friends and family discount. We are honored and we will take it.

00:01:46:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:46:150000.Dialogue: What are you doing? 250 is already the discounted price.

00:02:07:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:07:130000.Dialogue: Oh, now, we can't let him lose money, Leonard. I'm so sorry.

00:02:10:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:10:100000.Dialogue: 210 and you throw in the Iron Man helmet.

00:02:13:140000.Speaker: Stuart
00:02:13:140000.Dialogue: Are you crazy? That helmet's signed by Robert Downey Jr.

00:02:17:140000.Speaker: Stuart
00:02:17:140000.Dialogue: Okay, if you're going to question the importance of an actor's signature on a plastic helmet from a movie based on a comic book, then all of our lives have no meaning!

00:02:33:110000.Speaker: Stuart
00:02:33:110000.Dialogue: Thank you. I can eat meat this week.

00:02:38:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:38:100000.Dialogue: See that? I just saved us 40 bucks.

00:02:40:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:40:180000.Dialogue: I've long said, what you lack in academic knowledge you make up for in street smarts.

00:02:45:180000.Speaker: Stuart
00:02:45:180000.Dialogue: You want me to wrap it?

00:02:46:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:46:210000.Dialogue: No, it's okay. I'm gonna stab my friend in the chest.

00:03:00:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:00:030000.Dialogue: It's part of my sword collection. Do you have a sword collection?

00:03:07:110000.Speaker: Stuart
00:03:07:110000.Dialogue: Here's the Batman 612 with the Jim Lee alternate cover that you wanted.

00:03:12:100000.Speaker: Wil
00:03:12:100000.Dialogue: Awesome. What do I owe you?

00:03:16:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:16:030000.Dialogue: Sucker. Didn't even ask for the friends and family discount.

00:03:19:230000.Speaker: Wil
00:03:19:230000.Dialogue: Hey, I'm having a party at my house on Friday, and I was hoping you would stop by.

00:03:28:190000.Speaker: Wil
00:03:28:190000.Dialogue: There will be girls. You guys are invited if you want to come by.

00:03:40:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:40:120000.Dialogue: I see what you're doing. You accept an invitation to a party at the home of my sworn enemy, he tells everyone we're going to be there, and when we don't show, he looks the fool. Fiendishly clever.

00:03:52:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:52:160000.Dialogue: I was actually thinking about going.

00:03:54:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:54:080000.Dialogue: And then declaring the party a fiasco and storming out, leaving him humiliated in front of his guests. Love it.

00:04:02:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:02:190000.Dialogue: No, I was gonna grab Raj and Howard and have a good time.

00:04:07:160000.Speaker: Stuart
00:04:07:160000.Dialogue: Oh, great, more guys. It's gonna be another Wil Wheaton sausage-fest.

00:04:39:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:39:000000.Dialogue: Sheldon, can you grab me a water?

00:04:48:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:48:180000.Dialogue: SHELDON: At this moment, our relationship exists in two mutually contradictory states. Until you either do not go or go to Wil Wheaton's party, you are simultaneously my friend and not my friend.

00:05:03:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:03:120000.Dialogue: I'm characterizing this phenomenon as Schrodinger's Friendship.

00:05:08:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:08:060000.Dialogue: Got it. Can I have my water?

00:05:11:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:11:020000.Dialogue: Of course. Now get it yourself, you traitor.

00:05:19:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:19:170000.Dialogue: In case you have forgotten, Schrodinger's cat is a thought experiment...

00:05:22:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:22:160000.Dialogue: No, no, I didn't forget. Um, there's this cat in a box and until you open it, it's either dead or alive or both. Although, back in Nebraska, our cat got stuck in my brother's camp trunk, and we did not need to open it to know there was all kinds of dead cat in there.

00:05:37:230000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:37:230000.Dialogue: Homespun stories, knowledge of physics and a bosom that defies it. You're the whole package, aren't you?

00:05:46:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:46:230000.Dialogue: Uh, I got great news. NASA picked my team's design for the deep field space telescope that's going on the International Space Station this spring.

00:05:59:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:59:170000.Dialogue: It gets better. Someone has to go up with the telescope as a payload specialist, and guess who that someone is.

00:06:13:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:13:130000.Dialogue: Muhammad is the most common first name in the world, Li, the most common surname. As I didn't know the answer, I thought that gave me a mathematical edge.

00:06:21:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:21:200000.Dialogue: It's me, Sheldon. It's me. I'm going up in space! Technically, I'm an astronaut.

00:06:30:110000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:06:30:110000.Dialogue: Hang on a second. NASA doesn't have a shuttle anymore. How are you going to get up there?

00:06:35:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:35:220000.Dialogue: Oh, well, it's really cool. You fly to Moscow, they take you out to Kazakhstan, and then you get into a Russian Soyuz rocket which shoots you into a low earth orbit. Or just sits there on the launch pad because the Kazakhi mafia sold the rocket fuel on the black market.

00:06:52:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:52:050000.Dialogue: Well, I mean, safe as it can be when it was built by the good folks who brought you Chernobyl.

00:06:58:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:58:170000.Dialogue: I'd like to propose a toast. The dream to go up into space is one we all share, and Howard's making that a reality. We're all very proud of you.

00:07:10:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:10:110000.Dialogue: That was a lovely toast. Kudos.

00:07:12:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:12:230000.Dialogue: Simultaneously, a festival of cloying clichés. You sicken me.

00:07:24:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:24:160000.Dialogue: You're really quiet. Is everything okay?

00:07:34:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:34:140000.Dialogue: I hope not too tired, because I'm feeling particularly masculine right now.

00:07:40:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:40:090000.Dialogue: All systems go, if you catch my drift.

00:07:46:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:46:220000.Dialogue: All right, well, something's obviously bugging you. What is it?

00:07:50:230000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:07:50:230000.Dialogue: I just can't believe you signed up for the space program without even talking to me.

00:07:55:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:55:060000.Dialogue: Oh, I get it. You're worried about me. That is so sweet. You know, there's a saying we have at NASA.

00:08:10:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:10:020000.Dialogue: What makes the right stuff so right is that it always comes home.

00:08:21:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:21:210000.Dialogue: This isn't the reaction I expected when I told you I was gonna be an astronaut.

00:08:25:200000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:08:25:200000.Dialogue: What did you think was going to happen?

00:08:33:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:33:210000.Dialogue: Do you realize what a big deal this is? What an honor it is to be chosen to go into space?

00:08:39:150000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:08:39:150000.Dialogue: Yeah, I get it. I just wish you included me in the decision. We're supposed to be partners. We're supposed to be a team.

00:08:49:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:49:040000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. You're right. Okay, let's try this again. Bernadette, an opportunity has come up that impacts both of us, and I'd like to discuss it.

00:09:06:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:06:130000.Dialogue: I've been offered a chance to go up to the International Space Station for three weeks. What are your thoughts on that?

00:09:14:220000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:09:14:220000.Dialogue: Well, first of all, thank you for including me in the decision-making process.

00:09:20:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:20:210000.Dialogue: Hey, we're a team. So, what do you think?

00:09:36:100000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:09:36:100000.Dialogue: Howard, my father was a police officer. We never knew from one night to the next if he was going to come home alive. It was horrible. And I don't want to live that way with you.

00:09:50:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:50:200000.Dialogue: Hey, my father abandoned me and my mother when I was 11. We never saw him again.

00:09:59:090000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:09:59:090000.Dialogue: Oh, boo-hoo, you're not going to space!

00:10:09:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:09:140000.Dialogue: Don't talk to me as if nothing's happened between us. And yes, it sure is, buddy.

00:10:16:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:16:020000.Dialogue: For God's sake, will you stop with the Schroer stuff.

00:10:18:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:18:160000.Dialogue: Would you prefer a simpler application of Heisenberg's uncertainty principle, in which I could either know where you are or whether I like you, but not both?

00:10:27:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:27:070000.Dialogue: You never stop talking, do you?

00:10:31:230000.Speaker: Amy
00:10:31:230000.Dialogue: I don't understand. What differences does it make if Leonard goes to Wil Wheaton's party?

00:10:36:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:36:080000.Dialogue: Wil Wheaton is Sheldon's mortal enemy.

00:10:43:050000.Speaker: Amy
00:10:43:050000.Dialogue: you really have a mortal enemy?

00:10:46:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:46:230000.Dialogue: In fact, I have 61 of them.

00:10:50:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:50:040000.Dialogue: Would you like to see the list?

00:10:52:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:52:030000.Dialogue: Oh, say no, say no, say no, say no.

00:10:54:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:54:020000.Dialogue: You just got off the list. Would you like back on it?

00:10:58:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:58:140000.Dialogue: This'll just take a moment. It's on a five and a quarter inch floppy.

00:11:11:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:11:130000.Dialogue: Well, I started the list when I was nine.

00:11:15:030000.Speaker: Amy
00:11:15:030000.Dialogue: How did Wil Wheaton get on the list?

00:11:18:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:18:210000.Dialogue: As a child, I loved Wesley Crusher, Wil Wheaton's character on Star Trek. So, I drove for hours by bus to a Star Trek convention at which Wil Wheaton was scheduled to appear, so that I could get my Wesley Crusher action figure signed. But he never showed, because apparently, it was cooler for him to be the lower-left corner on Hollywood Squares.

00:11:42:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:42:120000.Dialogue: Oh, damn! The floppy failed. Well, whoever was in charge of quality control at the Verbatim Corporation in 1989, congratulations, you just made the list.

00:12:01:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:01:110000.Dialogue: I'm still mad, but I'll do it.

00:12:05:060000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:05:060000.Dialogue: No, I've just been thinking. It doesn't matter if I'm afraid for your safety. I don't want to be the person who stands between you and your dreams.

00:12:16:170000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:16:170000.Dialogue: Really. If going into space means that much to you, I will never say another word about it.

00:12:25:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:25:070000.Dialogue: I love you, too. So, sex now?

00:12:32:120000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:32:120000.Dialogue: Okay. I just forgot to brush my teeth. I'll be right back.

00:12:58:210000.Speaker: Mrs Wolowitz
00:12:58:210000.Dialogue: MRS. WOLOWITZ: Over my dead body my son goes into outer space!

00:13:12:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:12:110000.Dialogue: Wait, let me see if I got this right. You actually asked Bernadette to leave your house in the middle of the night?

00:13:16:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:16:160000.Dialogue: What choice did I have? She went behind my back and turned my own mother against me.

00:13:21:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:21:110000.Dialogue: Wow. You're not only our first astronaut. You're also the first one of us to kick a girl out of bed.

00:13:34:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:34:030000.Dialogue: I hate to say it, but she did kind of betray you.

00:13:37:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:37:060000.Dialogue: Interesting. You see betrayal in others, but not yourself.

00:13:42:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:42:230000.Dialogue: Going to Wheaton's party is not betraying you.

00:13:47:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:47:070000.Dialogue: Oh, of course you would have to believe that. Evil always thinks it's doing right.

00:13:52:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:52:170000.Dialogue: Excuse me, Stormtrooper. These are the droids you're looking for.

00:13:57:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:57:090000.Dialogue: I'm going to a party. I'm not turning R2-D2 and C-3PO over to the empire!

00:14:09:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:09:140000.Dialogue: So, what's gonna happen next? Are you and Bernadette going to break up?

00:14:12:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:12:160000.Dialogue: I don't know. If we're going to get back together, she's going to have to apologize and accept that I'm a grown man who can make his own decisions.

00:14:20:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:20:190000.Dialogue: Then she's going to have to convince your mother to let you go into space.

00:14:27:150000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:27:150000.Dialogue: I had no choice. I had to tell his mother. He can't go to space. He's like a baby bird.

00:14:38:010000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:38:010000.Dialogue: Do you know he once got an asthma attack from reading an old library book?

00:14:45:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:45:190000.Dialogue: No, I was there that day. Sheldon threw his back out handing him that book.

00:14:52:120000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:52:120000.Dialogue: I don't know what I'm going to do. I don't want to break up over this.

00:14:56:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:56:110000.Dialogue: Okay, why don't you just tell him you made a mistake?

00:14:58:150000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:58:150000.Dialogue: Do you guys think it was a mistake? Am I the bad guy in this?

00:15:03:090000.Speaker: Amy
00:15:03:090000.Dialogue: It's not for us to judge. We're just here to provide comfort and support while you come to grips with what a despicable thing you've done.

00:15:12:120000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:15:12:120000.Dialogue: Oh, God, you're right. I took our love and threw it under his bus-sized mother.

00:15:24:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:24:060000.Dialogue: Well, that-that's good. I'm glad you came to that. But before you do, let me just ask you a big picture question.

00:15:30:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:30:110000.Dialogue: Are you 100% positive you love and want to marry Howard Wolowitz?

00:15:37:060000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:15:37:060000.Dialogue: I do, with all my heart.

00:15:39:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:39:170000.Dialogue: Got it. Just had to check.

00:15:50:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:50:150000.Dialogue: All right, Sheldon. We're going to Wil's. This is your last chance.

00:15:55:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:55:100000.Dialogue: No, Leonard, this is your last chance. One day, a historian is going to come to you and say, Is it true you were friends with Dr. Sheldon Cooper? And you're going to have to choke back a hot sob of regret and humiliation as you mumble, I was, but I chose to go to a party thrown by the one kid from Stand By Me that no one remembers.

00:16:28:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:28:120000.Dialogue: Oh, good. You picked me, you picked me.

00:16:31:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:31:040000.Dialogue: No, I just got a text from Stuart. Brent Spiner is at the party.

00:16:41:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:41:030000.Dialogue: Really? Brent Spiner, Mr. Data himself. You love him.

00:16:46:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:46:070000.Dialogue: I did, but I think I've kind of outgrown Star Trek.

00:16:52:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:52:230000.Dialogue: You know, stock characters, ludicrous plots, beam me up. What a load of hooey.

00:16:59:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:59:230000.Dialogue: I'm going. Live long and prosper, Sheldon.

00:17:03:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:03:090000.Dialogue: Yeah, even that. You look like a dork.

00:17:14:020000.Speaker: Mrs Wolowitz
00:17:14:020000.Dialogue: What kind of a schmuck play is that?! She can hear you shouting!

00:17:22:010000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:22:010000.Dialogue: You can. I have nothing to say.

00:17:24:160000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:17:24:160000.Dialogue: All right. I just wanted to tell you I'm sorry I said something to your mother.

00:17:31:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:31:030000.Dialogue: I was gonna tell her eventually, but you went behind my back.

00:17:35:180000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:17:35:180000.Dialogue: I know. I'm sorry. I got scared.

00:17:39:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:39:020000.Dialogue: If you're gonna love me, you're gonna have to love the whole package: the tenderhearted poet and the crazy daredevil.

00:17:49:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:49:180000.Dialogue: Well, don't say it if you're not gonna mean it, 'cause I'm not just gonna stop with the space station. Yeah, I want to go to the Moon, I want to go to Mars. I want to take a one-man sub to the lowest depths of the ocean.

00:18:01:210000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:18:01:210000.Dialogue: Really? You got seasick on Pirates of the Caribbean.

00:18:06:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:06:200000.Dialogue: Well, those big kids were rocking it.

00:18:12:060000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:18:12:060000.Dialogue: I just did what I did because I love you so much, and the thought of losing you is more than I can handle.

00:18:20:140000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:18:20:140000.Dialogue: You're my soul mate. This is where you kiss me.

00:18:31:040000.Speaker: Mrs Wolowitz
00:18:31:040000.Dialogue: MRS. WOLOWITZ: Make up all you want! Your tuchis is not leaving this planet!

00:18:43:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:43:040000.Dialogue: Hey, you know that beautiful actress who plays the Borg Queen in First Contact?

00:18:55:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:55:120000.Dialogue: Fighting for our friendship. As peculiar and annoying as you can be, you're still my little buddy. I'm not going to let that end here tonight. Now put down that drink, let's meet Brent Spiner and go home.

00:19:08:070000.Speaker: Wil
00:19:08:070000.Dialogue: Hey, Sheldon, I'm so glad you made it. I found something I think you might like.

00:19:11:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:11:200000.Dialogue: What I'd like is for him to have a more depressing home. This is quite lovely.

00:19:19:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:19:190000.Dialogue: An original mint-in-package Wesley Crusher action figure.

00:19:23:170000.Speaker: Wil
00:19:23:170000.Dialogue: I remembered your story about the time you went to a convention when you were a kid to get one signed, and I didn't show up. Look at what I wrote.

00:19:30:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:30:060000.Dialogue: To Sheldon, sorry this took so long. Your friend, Wil Wheaton

00:19:36:060000.Speaker: Wil
00:19:36:060000.Dialogue: It's my last one. I want you to have it.

00:19:42:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:42:070000.Dialogue: Look, everyone. Wil Wheaton is my friend!

00:19:48:010000.Speaker: Brent Spiner
00:19:48:010000.Dialogue: Oh, wow. I haven't seen one of these in years.

00:19:54:120000.Speaker: Brent Spiner
00:19:54:120000.Dialogue: Remember how we used to make these things look like they were masturbating?

00:19:58:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:58:160000.Dialogue: Brent Spiner, what have you done?! That was an original mint-in-package Wesley Crusher action figure signed by my close personal friend, Wil Wheaton.

00:20:06:220000.Speaker: Brent
00:20:06:220000.Dialogue: Sorry, Slim. I've got some Mr. Data dolls in the trunk of my car. You want me to sign one for you?

00:20:12:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:12:030000.Dialogue: You've already signed something, Brent Spiner. Your name on my list.

00:20:19:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:19:110000.Dialogue: From this moment on, you are my mortal enemy.

00:20:21:130000.Speaker: Wil
00:20:21:130000.Dialogue: Don't worry. It doesn't take up a whole lot of your time.

00:20:25:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:25:070000.Dialogue: Come on, buddy. Let's not waste another second on this loser. Love your house.

00:20:48:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:48:170000.Dialogue: Two for $30. And you come to my birthday party.
